result.name: Pizza Maru

reviews.text: Very tasty food, it's a Seoul and western fusion cuisine. There were lots of handmade different taste of craft beers and different taste of fried chicken. We had ordered a pizza with beef and lots of ingredients with tomato sauce which was delicious and yummy. The creamy beet linguine with seared scallop was so special and great taste! Service and environment were great too! Must come again
I loved this place. Everything was perfect. Well it would be nice to be able to make my own custom pizza, but other than that I would be here all the time if I was a local.

Everything we had tried here was so delicious! Honey Butter Fried Chicken was the best I ever had. It’s crispy and tasty. Chessy Maru Oppa pizza was very appetizing. Plus the service was great. We will definitely come back here to try more stuff.

Had a pizza and fried chicken for dinner. They were both well made and very tasty, except that a strong aftertaste lingered in my mouth for hours. It might be the artificial seasonings and msg. Service was good. A pizza, 12 pieces of chicken plus a beer costed over $500.
Excellent Garlic Honey Korean Fried chicken, I must come back million times
